Fifty students from Kikambala have received full scholarships for secondary school from the Centum Foundation. A third of them are girls.They received the scholarships during the launch of Centum&rsquo;s The Vipingo Development Limited Scholarship Fund at Timboni Primary School in Kilifi county. The launch was presided over by Governor Amason Kingi.The chairman of Centum Investment Committee, Chris Kirubi, Centum Group CEO James Mworia and director of Centum Capital Fred Murimi were present. The fund will award 50 scholarships annually to students who score more than 300 marks in the KCPE exam. The number will rise to 200 by 2019.